content.description: Adds some great moves (and difficulty) into the existing classic.
content.location: Start way down and right—right-hand slot in seam and left hand in a good slot pocket.

content.description: One of the best V9s in Roy. Big dynamic moves to start into a compression sequence then a big lockoff to top out.The standard start is a stand with hueco. There is a sit start now however, which adds some nice moves, and a low start which adds about 8 moves on pockets, coming in from far right (V10/11).
content.protection: Needs 4-5 pads to adequately protect the angled ramp landing.

content.description: Clean horizontal roof with sharp pockets.SDS left hand sharp one/two finger pocket, right on blocky pinch. Big move to clover pocket and tough match. Continue out on edges. Has an easy but currently dirty topout on face.If you start on the clover pocket it's V9, People Are Strange.
content.location: Far right side of Big Fred's. Perfect flat landing.

content.description: Big, steep cave, contains the classic Spanish Caravan along with a number of double digit lines and projects.
